article.headline: Wright State 50, Detroit 49
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- DaShaun Wood scored 19 points, including the winning free throw, to lead Wright State to a come-from-behind win over Detroit 50-49 Saturday. Detroit (2-5, 0-1 Horizon League) led by 10 with just under 13 minutes to go when Wright State (2-2, 1-0) went on a 21-11 run to tie the game at 48 with 26 seconds left. Detroit took the lead back on a Chris Hayes free throw, then Wood was fouled by Brandon Cotton and sank both shots. The teams traded the lead four times in the first half, but Detroit was up 23-22 at halftime. Ryvon Covile led the Titans with 11 points and 12 rebounds, and Hayes added eight points and six rebounds. Vaughn Duggins had nine points for the Raiders, who shot about 32 percent to Detroit's nearly 44 percent. The Titans also outrebounded Wright State 35-27, but the Raiders were perfect from the free throw line.
